SIMPLE: corse
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corse
<hw>Corse</hw> <pr>(k?rs ⟦or⟧ k?rs; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>cors</ets>, F. <ets>corps</ets>. See <er>Corpse</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A living body or its bulk.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For he was strong, and of so mighty <qex>corse</qex>⟦br⟧
As ever wielded spear in warlike hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A corpse; the dead body of a human being.</def>
<mark>[Archaic or Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Set down the <qex>corse</qex>; or, by <person>Saint
Paul</person>,⟦br⟧
I'll make a <qex>corse</qex> of him that disobeys.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corselet</ent>⟦br⟧
